<SLUG> BC-BKO-BRUNNER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRUNNER FACES CHARGES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Kenny Brunner, who led Dominguez High to
back-to-back state basketball championships, will be in L.A.
Municipal Court this morning for a preliminary hearing to determine
whether he will stand trial on charges of attempted murder and
robbery of Los Angeles City College basketball coach Mike Miller.
</P>
<P>
   It is the latest in a rash of events that threaten to ruin
Brunner's once-promising career.
</P>
<P>
   He quit Georgetown's team in January, midway through his
freshman season, and later transferred to Fresno State, where he
was arrested in March along with former Artesia star Avondre Jones
on charges they robbed and assaulted a student with a samurai
sword. Brunner was suspended indefinitely from Fresno State's team
and then declared himself eligible for the NBA draft, a decision he
later reversed.
</P>
<P>
   Then, on May 22, Brunner was arrested for allegedly pointing a
semi-automatic handgun at Miller and pulling the trigger, but the
gun did not fire. Brunner, police say, then grabbed $1,500 from
Miller and fled.
</P>
<P>
   Brunner was arrested shortly after and is in L.A. County jail,
unable to post $550,000 bail. He has been charged with attempted
first-degree premeditated murder with a special allegation that he
used a firearm, and second-degree robbery.
</P>
<P>
   Also arrested was Ladale Lunnie, a LACC player, who was charged
with second-degree robbery and is free on $50,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Brunner, though his attorney Jerome Bradford, declined to be
interviewed.
</P>
<P>
   Dominguez coach Russell Otis, for whom Brunner played under for
four years, says he talks with his former player daily. (Inmates
are allowed collect phone calls.)
</P>
<P>
   ``He's trying to stay strong,'' Otis said. ``He reads the Bible,
plays some basketball and watches TV. Kenny's been catered to all
his life through basketball and then to be in this situation. It's
got to be traumatic.''
</P>
<P>
   Otis says Brunner has had contact with few others mainly his
family, attorney and Laker forward Mario Bennett, a longtime
friend.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's amazing how many people have turned their back on Kenny
and assumed he's guilty,'' said Otis. ``But that's the way our
society is you're guilty until proven innocent.''
</P>
<P>
   Today's hearing will determine if the District Attorney's office
has enough evidence to warrant a trial of Brunner or Lunnie. If so,
the matter will be transferred to Superior Court, where in two
weeks a trial date would be set. If the case goes to trial, it
would likely be 60 days beyond that, said both Bradford and
prosecutor Andrew Bassis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
