   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ As he aged, my father, who
lived to be 93, often commented on how little he understood of what
the world was coming to. ``Everything is end over apple cart,'' was
his way of expressing his puzzlement. Now I'm beginning to suspect
he was the neighborhood sage. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
