   SMART-HOMES01 _ From the outside, it looks like any
othertraditional home. But beneath the shingles and siding, it
contains the framework for the future. It's a ``smart house.''
Parents can keep tabs on the sleeping baby in the nursery by using
their TV. Mom can turn up the air conditioning or turn off the
lights over the phone while the family is on vacation. Teenagers
can surf the Internet while Dad sends e-mail to the office. The
family can feel like they're at the movies in their own living room
with a big-screen TV, surround sound and sub-woofers to capture
low-frequency effects such as the footsteps of Tyrannosaurus Rex in
``Jurassic Park.'' ``You feel the thumping,'' said home system
designer George Ide, vice president of Alpharetta, Ga.-based
Digital Interiors Inc., an authorized dealer for Smart House, Inc.
Homeowners in the metro Atlanta area are pleased with their
high-tech houses, but problems have surfaced elsewhere. (Crabb,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
