<SLUG> BC-MANGO-IDEAS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    40 ways to savor a mango
 &HT;    (With MANGO-RECIPES)
 &HT;    By Jan Norris
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Mango smoothies, mango bread, mango
wine, mango chutney, mango pie, mango cobbler, mango liqueur, mango
chips . . . enough already!
</P>
<P>
   For the first few weeks, mangoes are great, eaten right over the
sink, juice just dripping all over you and the floor. Then you
realize you're sick of them altogether. Trouble is, so is everyone
else on your list _ and you can't give 'em away.
</P>
<P>
   What to do?
</P>
<P>
   Here are 40 mango-related ideas. Take 'em _ or leave them for
someone else to pick.
</P>
<P>
   1) Gild your mangoes Martha Stewart-style. Then artfully arrange
them in a piece of pottery you've thrown yourself.
</P>
<P>
   2) Find all streets with ``mango'' in their name. (There are at
least 13 in Palm Beach County alone.)
</P>
<P>
   3) Bob for mangoes.
</P>
<P>
   4) Make a mango daiquiri. Per drink: 1 part mango puree, 1 part
good rum, 1 teaspoon of superfine sugar.
</P>
<P>
   5) Play ``Pass the Mango'': Everyone stands in a line. The first
person puts the mango under his/her chin and passes it to the next
person's chin, but no hands are allowed. Hint: Find people who
aren't allergic to mangoes.
</P>
<P>
   6) Donate mangoes to the Daily Bread Food Bank. Call (561)
659-5070 for details.
</P>
<P>
   7) String one up on a pole for the dog to chase.
</P>
<P>
   8) Stuff your bra.
</P>
<P>
   9) Organize a mango baseball game.
</P>
<P>
   10. Start a Take-Your-Mango-To-Work Day.
</P>
<P>
   11) Get on the Internet and find all the mango-related Web
pages.
</P>
<P>
   12) Grow a Chia-Mango. Pare the skin off one side of the mango.
Sprinkle it with alfalfa seeds. Keep wet. Trim as needed.
</P>
<P>
   13) Stage the first worldwide Mango Summer Games, and have
events such as mango-relay, mango-toss and mango-lifting.
</P>
<P>
   14) Wear a Carmen Miranda-style mango hat.
</P>
<P>
   15) Throw a mango margarita party. Play Jimmy Buffett's Last
Mango in Paris.
</P>
<P>
   16) Walk into the local allergy clinic and hold up a mango.
Shout, ``This is a stick-up! I have a ripe mango, and I'm not
afraid to use it!''
</P>
<P>
   17) Next time you're in the mall, make trouble by insisting on a
Mango Julius.
</P>
<P>
   18) Make your own Mr. Mango Head.
</P>
<P>
   19) Perfect the art of peeling a mango. There is a flat side to
every mango _ find it and slice vertically down that side. Turn the
mango 180 degrees and slice down the other side of the pit. Pull
out the pit _ you now have two juicy halves. Make cross-hatches
through the fruit flesh just to the skin on both sides, and flip
the skin inside-out.
</P>
<P>
   20) Take your mangoes to a road-building site and drop a few
under a steamroller.
</P>
<P>
   21) String dried mango pits for your next Christmas tree.
</P>
<P>
   22) Mang-O-War! Buy big slingshots and fire away.
</P>
<P>
   23) Make a fruity baby. Dress up a big mango in a baby hat and
glue booties to its bottom. Swaddle it in a blanket, pop it in the
stroller, and see if anyone notices.
</P>
<P>
   24) Count all the mango trees in Mangonia Park.
</P>
<P>
   25) Make mango leather: Dry very thin mango slices on a wire
rack for at least 8 hours in a 200 oven till leathery.
</P>
<P>
   26) Mango lawn bowling.
</P>
<P>
   27) Slice up a bunch of mangoes and serve them on little
toothpicks in your grocery store. Hand out coupons for free
mangoes.
</P>
<P>
   28) Mango croquet.
</P>
<P>
   29) Make up a mango tongue-twister and say it 10 times fast: My
mellow mother makes mango mustard mighty merrily.
</P>
<P>
   30) Launch a campaign to change the Orange Bowl to the Mango
Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   31) Fling mangoes at a canvas while friends beat on drums. Call
it performance art.
</P>
<P>
   32) Save water! Put mangoes in your toilet tank.
</P>
<P>
   33) Are your kids getting bored? Smash rotten mangoes on the
lawn for an instant run-and-slide.
</P>
<P>
   34) Have a ``My Mango's Bigger Than Yours'' contest.
</P>
<P>
   35) Make mango smoothies: Mangoes and frozen yogurt, or mangoes,
ice and plain yogurt.
</P>
<P>
   36) Hunt down that famous Sports Illustrated swimsuit issue with
the mango-eating model in it.
</P>
<P>
   37) Do the mango-tango! Put the mangoes all over the floor.
Learn to dance the tango by avoiding the fruit.
</P>
<P>
   38) Spray paint mangoes in a terra-cotta color. Use them to edge
your flower beds.
</P>
<P>
   39) Lobby the legislature for a mango license plate.
</P>
<P>
   40) Save the mangoes! Plant your own tree.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
