lately. What's unusual about that is that they've done it in a
still-strong stock market. ``Utilities have been the
best-performing sector of the market for the last four weeks,''
said Hugh Johnson, chief investment officer at First Albany Corp.
in Albany, N.Y. By PAMELA YIP.
</P>
