from ``Boss of the Plains: That Hat that won the West'' to ``Black
Cowboy, Wild Horses: A True Story.'' By JANE P. MARSHALL.
</P>
<P>
   O'SULLIVAN-FUNERAL (Colonie, N.Y.) _ Maureen O'Sullivan played
many roles during her acting career. But it was her role as a
mother that mourners remembered at her funeral at Siena College
here. By KIMBERLY MARTINEAU.
</P>
<P>
   WOODSTOCK (Bethel, N.Y. ) _ With a $69.98 ticket and proper
credentials, you'll be able to get near the natural amphitheater on
Max Yasgur's farm, the site of the original Woodstock Music and Art
Fair in 1969, for ``A Day in the Garden,'' featuring some of the
legendary music festival's original acts. The event is set for Aug.
14-15, the 29th anniversary of the first Woodstock. By JAY
JOCHNOWITZ.
</P>
