<P>
   States News Service
</P>
<P>
   CORRECTION TO WASHINGTON WATCH VOTE CHART Questions regarding
this transmission should be directed to 202-628-3100, ext. 224.
WASHINGTON, June 30 -- The following is a correction to last week's
vote chart regarding the ``IRSREFORM'' bill. The chart shows how
house representatives voted on the IRS reform bill. A ``Y'' means
the member voted for the measure; an ``N'' means the member voted
against the measure; a ``?'' means the member did not vote; and a
``P'' means the member voted ``present.''
</P>
<P>
   THERE ARE NO SENATE VOTES THIS WEEK.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE VOTES:
</P>
<P>
   1) BILL NUMBER: IRSREFORM
</P>
<P>
   The House voted Thursday, 402-8, to pass an IRS overhaul and tax
bill. The measure would establish a citizens' oversight panel and
increase taxpayer rights in collection disputes with the IRS.
Supporters said the bill would protect taxpayers from any abuse
from the tax agency. Opponents objected to a measure that shortens
the capital gains holding period from 18 months to 12 months to
escape financial penalties, calling it a tax break for the wealthy.
A ``yes'' vote favors the bill.
</P>
<P>
   VOTE : 1
</P>
<P>
   ---
</P>
<P>
   BORSKI (D-PA) Y
</P>
<P>
   COYNE (D-PA) Y
</P>
<P>
   DOYLE (R-PA) Y
</P>
<P>
   ENGLISH (R-PA) Y
</P>
<P>
   FATTAH (D-PA) ?
</P>
<P>
   FOGLIETTA (D-PA) O
</P>
<P>
