<P>
   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SHANGHAI (Shanghai, China) _ already filed _ President
and Mrs. Clinton treat 10 million radio talk-show listeners to
details about their personal lives in an effort that the White
House spokesman says was designed to overcome any distrust by the
Chinese public. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   YEAR-2000 (Washington) _ The National Association of
Manufacturers calls the Year 2000 computer glitch a ``disaster in
the making'' and accuses President Clinton of failing to make the
computer bug a national priority. By MARK HELM. Story also will be
filed in the Financial News, or ``f,'' category.
</P>
<P>
   FLAG-BURNING (WASHINGTON) _ Fighting a proposed constitutional
amendment to ban flag burning, a group releases a TV ad in the
states of Washington, Oregon and North Dakota. The group, People
for the American Way, which seeks to preserve First Amendment
freedoms, wants to persuade senators in the states to vote against
the measure. By NICOLE TSONG.
