</P>
<P>
   HILTON-CASINOS (Los Angeles) _ Hilton announces that it is into
separate hotel and casino operations and will buy three Mississippi
properties from Grand Casinos Inc. for $650 million. By Andrew
Pollack.
</P>
<P>
   OIL-ROUGH-NECKS (Abilene, Texas) _ Many ``rough necks'' _
laborers on oil rigs _ lost their jobs when oil prices hit bottom
in the late 1980s. Such a big glut of workers was created that for
years new opportunities in the field were almost nonexistent. When
prices strengthened several years ago, though, the oil-service
companies suddenly found that a whole generation of workers had
vanished, and they have been scrambling ever since to catch up. Oil
prices have fallen again, but this time, some industry executives
argue, the pool of skilled workers has shrunk so much that the
labor shortage will persist for at least several years. By Agis
Salpukas.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS-TRAVEL (Undated) _ The Business Travel column: A
construction project at the Westchester County Airport will be
finished next month, to the great relief of the business travelers
who use the airport; other items.
