<HEADLINE>
LOTTO SUPPORTS GROUP FOR COMPULSIVE GAMBLERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What is the name of the organization that the lottery funds
to help people with gambling problems? How many calls does it get?
</P>
<P>
   _ K.L., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The group is the Texas Council on Problem and Compulsive
Gambling, and it fields about 4,000 calls per month.
</P>
<P>
   However, 90 to 95 percent of the callers want information on how
to play the lottery, said council director Sue Cox. The remaining
200 to 400 calls each month are from people seeking help with a
gambling problem.
</P>
<P>
   The help line, which opened on the same day (May 29, 1992) as
the state's lottery program, is printed on all Lotto and
scratch-off game tickets. The group receives $350,000 in funding
each year from lottery proceeds.
</P>
<P>
   To contact the council for help, call (800) 742-0443.
</P>
<P>
   Q: The news show ``Dateline'' featured a story about vitamins
that could be used to alleviate arthritis. What information is
available about this?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.F., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: According to NBC's Web site for ``Dateline,'' the information
you're seeking is in two books by Dr. Jason Theodosakis.
</P>
<P>
   In ``The Arthritis Cure,'' Theodosakis discusses the benefits of
taking glucosamine and chondroitin sulfates.
</P>
<P>
   The book claims that these supplements can rebuild lost bone
cartilage and provide relief to those suffering from
osteoarthritis. A follow-up book is titled ``Maximizing the
Arthritis Cure.''
</P>
<P>
   More information is available from Theodosakis at
www.drtheo.com. Or write to Jason Theodosakis, 6890 E. Sunrise, No.
120-383, Tucson, AZ 85750.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is the director Betty Thomas the same person who appeared on
``Hill Street Blues'' for many years?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.S., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: It is. Thomas has become a busy director in the '90s after a
13-year acting career, with credits that included ``Hill Street
Blues,'' ``Troop Beverly Hills'' and ``Used Cars.''
</P>
<P>
   Thomas directed this year's ``Doctor Dolittle.'' She also
directed ``Private Parts,'' ``The Late Shift'' and ``The Brady
Bunch Movie.'' She turns 51 on July 27.
</P>
<P>
   Write to Thomas in care of ICM, 8942 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly
Hills, CA 90211.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
