. &QL; 
JOE-DANCE (Los Angeles) _ Joe Siracusa of Tarzana used to be
drummer and provide all those wacky special sound effects for the
Spike Jones band, and later did cartoon voices for such characters
as the Hee Haw donkey and Fat Albert. Now a new widower with the
sole care of a disabled son, he makes time to teach twice-weekly
dance classes for seniors at a Reseda senior center. By Carol
Bidwell. &QL; 
. &QL;
