<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-30 17:57 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4368 &Cx1f; tic-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ROOTRECIPE-AZR &LR;      06-30 0261
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ROOTRECIPE-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROOT BEER PRAWN TEMPURA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (Undated) - (From Virgil's Root Beer) &QL; 
12 ounces (16-20) shrimp
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces self-rising flour
</P>
<P>
   2 ounces corn starch
</P>
<P>
   1 ounce baking powder
</P>
<P>
   3 ounces root beer, ice cold
</P>
<P>
   2 quarts of cooking oil in a heavy-gauge pot
</P>
<P>
   Peel and devein shrimp, leaving on tails. Dry and keep cold.
</P>
<P>
   Sift dry ingredients together.
</P>
<P>
   Heat the oil to 375 degrees on stove.
</P>
<P>
   Just before serving, place shrimp in bowl with dry ingredients.
Add ice-cold root beer quickly, in small amounts. Mix well until an
even coating consistency is achieved. Drop coated shrimp into hot
oil by tail. Fry until puffy and golden. Remove from oil and drain
on paper towels. Keep warm. Serve with root-beer dipping sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings. Approximate values per serving: 465 calories,
15 g fat, 129 mg cholesterol, 61 g carbohydrates, 623 mg sodium, 29
percent calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   Dipping Sauce
</P>
<P>
   (From Virgil's Root Beer)
</P>
<P>
   Zest and juice from 2 mandarin oranges
</P>
<P>
   16 ounces root beer
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sesame seeds, toasted
</P>
<P>
   Cut zest into julienne strips and blanch in boiling water for 10
seconds. Drain. Simmer root beer, blanched zest, sugar and juice
until reduced by half. Add sesame seeds. Sauce should have a light,
syrupy consistency.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings. Approximate values per serving: 89 calories, 1
g fat, 0 mg cholesterol, 19 g carbohydrates, 10 mg sodium, 13
percent calories from fat.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
