MENTAL CRUELTY (Phoenix) - We hear a lot about the physical side of
domestic abuse, but the mental cruelty - ranging from the mean to
the bizarre - leaves wounds and scars that often endure much
longer. By GINGER SCOTT. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
CRIME STOPPER (Phoenix) - Alvin Moses says Phoenix cops' new
crime-fighting approach has worked in his neighborhood. Since
police stopped arresting drug dealers, gang members, and armed
robbers one at a time and attacked the dens from which they dealt
death and dope, life has become a lot more peaceful. Police say
that, in fact, crime has gone down 31 percent in three central
Phoenix neighborhoods where they fought crime by taking a tough
stance against the apartments from which the crime emanated. It's
part of a nationwide crimefighting stragegy. By WILLIAM HERMANN.
Story will move in the ``A`` category.  &QL; 
