<SLUG> BC-LIBERTY-SUMMIT-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LIBERTY MUTUAL TO BUY FLORIDA WORKERS' COMP INSURER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By LYNNLEY BROWNING  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Liberty Mutual Group, an insurance and financial services firm,
agreed Tuesday to acquire Summit Holding Southeast Inc., a workers'
compensation insurance company in Lakeland, Fla., for nearly $223
million.
</P>
<P>
   The deal gives Liberty Mutual, A Boston company that is already
the nation's largest workers' compensation insurer, a greater share
of that competitive market.
</P>
<P>
   Liberty Mutual, with $51 billion in assets under management, has
expanded through acquisitions in recent years. Its Liberty
Financial Cos. Inc. subsidiary includes Colonial Group Inc., a
bond-oriented house, Chicago investment firm Stein Roe &AMP; Farnham,
Asian equities firm Newport Pacific Management, and Keyport Life
Insurance Co. of Boston.
</P>
<P>
   Summit will become a wholly owned independent subsidiary of
Liberty, whose insurance unit is Liberty Mutual Insurance Co. The
insurance company is owned by policy holders and is not publicly
traded.
</P>
<P>
   Under Tuesday's transaction, which values Summit at a 28 percent
premium above its closing price on Monday, Liberty will pay $33 per
Summit share. It will also redeem $17 million worth of Summit
preferred stock as well as assume $14.3 million in Summit debt. The
deal is expected to close in the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Summit is the third-largest workers' compensation insurer in
Florida and has 7 percent of the state's market. Tuesday's deal is
evidence of a consolidating financial services industry.
</P>
<P>
   The highly-regulated workers' compensation market varies greatly
according to state. In Massachusetts, insurers have complained that
rising compensation claims and a backlog of cases are eating up
profits.
</P>
<P>
   Summit rose 23 percent on Monday's close to finish Tuesday at 31
7/8 in heavy over-the-counter trading.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-30-98 1935EDT &QL; 
