 &HT;    On Deck: Braves vs. Devil Rays
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ When: 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Tropicana Field.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV, radio: Fox Sports South.
</P>
<P>
   _ Probable starting pitchers: RHP John Smoltz (5-2, 3.77 ERA;
first appearance vs. Devil Rays) vs. RHP Julio Santana (2-1, 5.11;
first appearance vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: Smoltz is making his 11th start and his third since his
second stint on the disabled list. His ERA, at 3.77, is as high as
it has been this season because of the pair of two-run homers he
gave up against Toronto in his last start. Despite that 6-4 loss,
Smoltz remains encouraged about the condition of his right elbow,
which needed rest for a week in late May. He threw a season-high
111 pitches against the Blue Jays with no discomfort and has not
lost his fastball, striking out 18 _ including 10 Blue Jays _ in
the 14 innings he has pitched since coming off the DL on June 20.
Santana, a Texas castoff, is making his fifth start but already has
shown why the Rangers sent him away. A converted shortstop, he
continues to have control problems (24 walks in 49 1/3 innings),
which make him more vulnerable when he pitches over the plate (52
hits allowed, including eight homers).
</P>
