<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by clients of the New York Times News Service)  
 
 Banker Quattrone Leaving Deutsche   By Tom Abate  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
 
After months of vehement denials, investment banker Frank Quattrone
and two colleagues abruptly quit the Deutsche Morgan Grenfell
Technology Group yesterday, leaving its future in doubt.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Quattrone and fellow bankers Bill Brady and George Boutros
disclosed their intention in a midday voicemail message sent to
DMG's 160 employees in Menlo Park.
</P>
<P>
   According to sources familiar with the voicemail, Quattrone said
the trio had decided to join Credit Suisse First Boston, which has
a local office in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   Quattrone, who formed the DMG Group two years ago, reportedly
apologized for the sudden departure, and said his contract with DMG
prevented him from offering his erstwhile associates jobs with his
new employer.
</P>
<P>
   The high-profile exodus was confirmed by Macy Egerton, a
spokeswoman for Deutsche Bank Securities, parent company of the DMG
Technology Group in Menlo Park.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've been informed of their intention to leave the firm,''
Edgerton said.
</P>
<P>
   The DMG Technology Group was born in controversy two years ago.
In what has been called the ``Easter Massacre,'' Quattrone led a
mass defection from the San Francisco offices of the Morgan Stanley
investment bank.
</P>
<P>
   What lured Quattrone was a multimillion-dollar offer to set up
his own Silicon Valley investment banking operation under the
auspices of Deutsche Morgan Grenfell, a huge German bank that
wanted to buy a presence in the high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
   Yesterday, dazed employees in Menlo Park tried to digest the
news, which came as a shock because Quattrone had spent the last
few months denying reports that he was having trouble with his
German bosses, and that he, Brady and Boutros were planning to jump
ship.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're just sitting here and waiting to see what happens,''
said one source. ``A lot of people are packing their boxes.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
