<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Fleming Cos., Oklahoma City, a food distributor, sold its supply
center in El Paso, Texas, to Furr's Supermarkets Inc., Albuquerque,
N.M., for as much as $45 million as part of a lawsuit settlement.
</P>
<P>
   Lear Corp., Southfield, Mich., an independent auto parts maker,
said it expected labor strikes against General Motors Corp. to cut
14 cents a share from its second-quarter earnings.
</P>
<P>
   LeCroy Corp., Chestnut Ridge, N.Y., a maker of scientific
instruments, will lay off an additional 90 full- and part-time
employees as it completes a previously announced restructuring to
cut costs. &QL;
</P>
