<SLUG> BC-HOLOCAUST-SCHOLAR-RESIGN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOLOCAUST SCHOLAR QUITS MUSEUM POST  
 (JT) 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Calif.)   c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Expressing ``deep regret,'' the United States
Holocaust Museum Tuesday accepted the resignation of John Roth,
whose appointment as the head of a new center for Holocaust
scholarship ran into severe criticism from some Jewish groups who
said he had made inappropriate comments about the Holocaust and who
campaigned for his ouster.
</P>
<P>
   Critics of Roth, chairman of the department of philosophy and
religious studies at Claremont McKenna College in Claremont,
Calif., said their campaign against Roth had paid off and they
praised him for resigning.
</P>
<P>
   Museum officials said in a statement they were ``saddened'' by
Roth's resignation.
</P>
<P>
   Roth's resignation comes after several weeks of controversy in
which some Jewish groups said Roth, in articles written years ago,
made inappropriate analogies involving the Holocaust. For instance,
they criticized him for comparing, in a 1988 article, the treatment
of Jews in Nazi Germany to Israel's treatment of Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
   Roth had been working with museum officials to establish within
the museum an international Center of Advanced Holocaust Studies,
which would train scholars in Holocaust research.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
