<HEADLINE>
ADVERTISING NOTES 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   OMNICOM AND OTHERS WIN AWARDS
</P>
<P>
   The New York Festivals has named six grand Best of Show winners
in its 41st annual international print and radio competition.
</P>
<P>
   TBWA/Campaign Co. in Amsterdam, part of the TBWA Worldwide unit
of Omnicom Group, won for best magazine campaign for an ad for
Samsonite Corp.
</P>
<P>
   Clemenger Melbourne Pty. in Melbourne, Australia, also part of
Omnicom, won for best newspaper ad for work for Yellow Pages
Australia.
</P>
<P>
   Interbrand Newell &AMP; Sorrell in London, another Omnicom unit, won
for best design for a corporate identity campaign for British
Airways.
</P>
<P>
   BBDO Canada in Toronto, part of the BBDO Worldwide unit of
Omnicom, won for best transit advertising, for the Pepsi-Cola Co.
unit of Pepsico Inc. JvM Werbeagentur GmbH in Hamburg, Germany, won
for best public service advertising for an advocacy effort to
promote the humane treatment of animals.
</P>
<P>
   And BLGK Advertising in Johannesburg, South Africa, part of the
Bates Worldwide unit of Cordiant Communications Group PLC, won the
grand award for radio commercials for a spot for The Financial Mail
publication.
</P>
<P>
   ACCOUNTS
</P>
<P>
   _ Opryland Hospitality and Attractions Group, Nashville, Tenn.,
a division of Gaylord Entertainment Co., to Buntin Group,
Nashville, to handle its advertising and public relations for
properties including the Opryland Hotel, which had been handled by
Ericson Marketing Communications, Nashville. Billings were
estimated at $2 million to $3 million. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
