QUOTATION OF THE DAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-HONGKONG-ANNIVERSARY-NYT, which
moved in ``i'' news file.)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Hong Kong is a graveyard for political prognosticators.
Everybody predicted we'd have a bumpy ride politically but the
economy would take care of itself. Exactly the opposite has
happened.''
</P>
<P>
   _DANIEL R. FUNG, solicitor general of Hong Kong.
</P>
