<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COX-BAHRAIN-GLANCEBOX-$ADV03 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;    BAHRAIN AT A GLANCE
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With BAHRAIN-DEMOCRACY-$ADV03 
 &HT;    For release July 03-06 
 &HT;    By LARRY KAPLOW 
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   STATE OF BAHRAIN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Group of 33 islands _ only six inhabited _ in the Persian Gulf.
Connected to Saudi Arabia by a 15-mile causeway.
</P>
<P>
   TOTAL SIZE: 268 square miles, about four times the size of
Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   POPULATION: About 586,000 in 1996, with one-third non-native.
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION: Approaching 80 percent literacy rate. High university
attendance.
</P>
<P>
   CULTURE: Arabic speakers; about two-thirds are Shia Muslims;
other third, including the rulers, are Sunni Muslims.
</P>
<P>
   INCOME: $8,262 per capita.
</P>
<P>
   MAJOR INDUSTRIES: Oil, aluminum, banking.
</P>
<P>
   GOVERNMENT: Monarchy under the Al Khalifa family and Amir Sheikh
Isa bin Sulman Al Khalifa and his brother, Prime Minister Khalifa
bin Sulman Al Khalifa. No political parties. The Al Khalifa's
dissolved the elected parliament in 1973.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. TIES: Host to the U.S. Navy Fifth Fleet; strong supporter
of U.S. military build-ups during U.S. confrontations with Iraqi
leader Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
   Source: U.S. Department of State.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
